race.comment: CELESTIAL GLOW (9) rates well and third-up should be ready to fire. Has been well supported both starts back and will likely be suited back in trip. Positions forward and has the winkers on for the first time. SMASH 'N' GRAB (8) resumes. Wasn't far away at her last run before a break and owns a Longford trial win. The 2kg claim is handy and she has the early speed to clear the awkward gate. Should be right in the finish. GEEGEES MERCEDES (10) resumes and won a recent Longford trial by 4.5L. Draws an inside gate and can return improved. PACIFIC WITNESS (12) debuts and Pires sticks from a Longford trial placing. The betting will be key.
